# Avoid Trivial Wrapper Functions

Do not create exported wrapper functions that only forward arguments to another function or method and return the result unchanged.

Prefer one of these instead:

- Export the underlying repository or object directly.
- Re-export the original symbol directly.
- Add a wrapper only when it adds real behavior such as validation, orchestration, transformation, retries, or access control.

```ts
// BAD
export function listEmailAddresses(): Promise<EmailAddressRecord[]> {
  return defaultEmailAddressRepository.listEmailAddresses();
}
```

```ts
// GOOD
export const emailAddressRepository: EmailAddressRepository =
  defaultEmailAddressRepository;

// GOOD: wrapper adds real behavior
export async function createEmailAddress(active = true): Promise<EmailAddressRecord> {
  const emailAddressRecord =
    await defaultEmailAddressRepository.createEmailAddress(active);
  await provisionIdentityEmailRouting(emailAddressRecord);
  return emailAddressRecord;
}
```
